                "COMMUNITY MEMBERS (NOVICES) AND EX-MINERS (DATABASE REGISTRATION) \u2013 FREE STATE REGION\nListing reference: hgcom_000006\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 22 March 2024\n \nPOSITION SUMMARY\nIndustry: Mining & Quarrying\nJob category: Drilling\nLocation: Welkom Thabong\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: No\n \nABOUT OUR COMPANY\nHarmony Gold Community Platform\n \nINTRODUCTION\nDatabase registration\n \nJOB DESCRIPTION\n\u00d8  Be able to fulfil required roles and responsibilities as per skills (novice/ex miner).\n\u00d8  Participate in Learning, demonstrate skills and be able to transfer those skills in the workplace.\n\u00d8  Be able to communicate, give instructions and follow up on instructions given.\n\u00d8  Demonstrate progress towards achievement of the training outcomes.\n\u00d8  Comply with the relevant assessment requirements.\n\u00d8  Follow a structured program, which contains on and off the job training.\n\u00d8  Be actively involved in personal development and drive own development.\n\u00d8  Carry out responsibilities as per type of work.\n\u00d8  Work the required shift cycle as per operational requirement.\n\u00d8  Ensure compliance with Health and Safety responsibilities.\n\u00d8  Comply with provided rules, systems, practices, methods, standards and procedures of the Company.\n\u00d8  Ensure and maintain effective communication.\n\u00d8  Ensure that the objectives and targets for the shift is achieved.\n\u00d8  Maintain Teamwork.\nLive the values of the Company.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\n\u00b7         The age limit will be 35 years for novices and 45 years for skilled candidates\n\u00b7         Grade 12 certificate and reference to the High School attended\n\u00b7         Ex miners:  Valid Certificates of competence as per skill and record of service\n\u00b7         Must be a local citizen from your Region\n\u00b7         Letter from your ward councillor stating ward number /district\n\u00b7         Must be South African Citizen with valid proof of identity\n\u00b7         Water and light account as proof of residence/address verification cert from CES\n\u00b7         Proficient in English speaking\n\u00b7         Ability to pass an underground Certificate of Fitness\n\u00b7         Need to pass Security Screening (No fraud, theft or violence)",
                "The following documentation need to be attached to your application:\n\u00d8  Signed CV (by CES)\n\u00d8  Address verification certificate or letter signed by the recognized community engagement structure, ward councillors or Traditional Council\n\u00d8  ID copy\n\u00d8  Highest Education or any other qualification certificates / degrees\n\n\u00d8  Other Skills training certificates (in the case of ex miners)\n\n \nApplications without relevant certified copies will not be considered.\n \nApplications will be added to the Community database and positions will be offered once available.\n \nYour application will be subjected to medical screening, Security screening and other verifications/assessments without creating the expectation of being a successful candidate. \nBy applying, you are giving consent to the above. \n \nAPPLY"
