                " \n \nQA/QC OFFICER - OPTIPOWER WOLF\nListing reference: mr_001561\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 22 March 2024\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Electricity, Energy & Water Supply\nJob category: Energy and Power Engineering\nLocation: Gqeberha (Port Elizabeth)\nContract: Fixed Term Contract\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nThe QA/QC officer will be responsible for capturing, reviewing and maintain the control of project quality documents . Successful candidate will also Interpret, build upon and comply with company and client quality standards, carefully maintain non- conformance processing through records and tracking systems. He or she will also document quality assurance activities with internal reporting and audits Avoid unnecessary work deviations or non-conformities\n \nJob description\nKey Performance Indicators: \n\nControl and distribution of all quality documentation on site\nMonitor all quality related activities on site\nTo ensure quality inspections are done in accordance to the stages of construction activities\nMonitoring of construction activities\nElimination of issues to ensure client requirements are continually met\nAttend all site meetings\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nMaintain the QC management system on site\nManage the document process\nCo-ordinate quality inspections with client and/or contractor\nCo-ordinate with the client representative and Employer on all quality matters\nCo-ordinate all receiving inspections\nDistribute relevant QC documentation to supervisors and contractors and ensure Transmittals are kept on the Quality Files and Folders\nVerify that the quality related site activities are in accordance with the applicable requirements and standards as per the agreed QC and ITP process between the client and the Employer\nParticipate in site internal and external audits\nCo-ordinate all the quality inspections through the Client\u2019s Site Representatives\nEnsure all quality control documentation is completed and signed for as-built hand over.\n Ensure that AS Built Drawings are issued by the design engineers.\nEnsure all quality data packs are completed, signed and submitted for invoicing progressively\nControl all non-conformance reports and undertake remedial action\nUpdate NCR Register\nReview the client\u2019s specification, drawings and Design packages and ensure Supervisors comply\nCo-ordinate with the Construction Manager on all quality issues\nEnsure that quality records, inspection check sheets, acceptance certificates, hand over certificates, completion certificates and the documentation for specific activities are prepared and collated in accordance with the project requirements\nCo-ordinate with the SHEQ and Project Managers for the completion of as-built hand over documentation\nResolve any discrepancies between the completed milestones and quality documentation submitted\nParticipate in the reviewing of supplier\u2019s and contractor\u2019s inspection and test plans against the scope of work\nAssist Supervisors and contractors to compile documentation for handover\nMonitor and control the status of punch lists and exception lists\nProvide progress data to the Construction Manager in a Monthly Quality Report\n \nCompetency Profile\nAttributes:\nGood communicative and interpersonal skills\nOutput driven\nGood Problem solving\nQuality conscious\nAttentive to detail\nBe able to work under pressure\nPlanning and Setting Priorities\nInitiative\nTeam Player\nAbility to correctly interpret drawings\n \nMinimum requirements\nExperience:\nMinimum of 3 years relevant experience as a QC officer in the Construction Industry \nExtensive knowledge and experience in the Renewable Energy field of Wind Farms\nGood Administrative skills\nComputer literate\nValid Driver\u2019s license\nMust be able to work independently as well as within a team\nExperience with internal and external audits\n \nQualifications:\nDiploma or similar qualification in Civils or Electrical\nISO 9001:2015 (advantageous)\n \nLocation \n200 kilometers away from Gqeberha (Port Elizabeth)\n \nAll appointments will be filled in line with our employment equity plan.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your application unsuccessful\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nGROUP REPORTING FINANCIAL ACCOUNTANT\nListing reference: mr_001559\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 22 March 2024\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Auditing/Accounting\nJob category: Accounting, Auditing\nLocation: Bedfordview\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nMurray & Roberts Corporate Office has a vacancy for a recently qualified CA (SA) or an individual who is eligible to register as a CA(SA). This position requires an individual with strong interpersonal skills, who is quality and deadline focused, with the drive for continuous improvement. This is an excellent opportunity for an individual, to join a large listed Group. The position has excellent career growth potential, as the individual will be exposed to all the entities and various service lines within the group. This position will be based at Head Office in Bedfordview, Johannesburg.\n \nJob description\nPreparation of Group consolidation for monthly results, quarterly assessments and business plans (3 year budgets) and the analysis of these results.\nPreparation of management reports used for i.e. board meetings at Group level.\nPreparation of Group and company annual financial statements.\nEnsure Group compliance with IFRS.\nProvide accounting advice to entities and senior management, with regards to the accounting impact that certain decisions may or may not have, depending on the decision they implement.\nUpdating the packs to be submitted by entities to ensure Group compliance of IFRS and that the necessary information is available for the consolidated annual financial statement.\nManagement / review of press release with regards to half year and year end results.\nPreparation of presentations for CFO required for board and external meetings.\nOther adhoc projects as requested by Group CFO\n \nEducation: Qualified CA (SA)\n \nMinimum requirements\nTeam player\nAbility to work efficiently and accurately under pressure\nStrong analytical skills set\nKnowledge of Excel (V-lookups, Sum-if and pivot tables) is a requirement\nPower Point & Hyperion knowledge is an advantage\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n ",
                "PROJECT COORDINATOR\nListing reference: mr_001560\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 20 March 2024\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Mining & Quarrying\nJob category: Other: Mining\nLocation: Rustenburg\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nMurray & Roberts Cementation invites suitably qualified candidates to apply for the position of Project Coordinator to be placed in Impala 16 Shaft. The successful candidate will report to the Project manager. The company will provide remuneration and benefits relevant and appropriate to the position. Preference will be given to Historically Disadvantaged South African (HDSA) candidates. Applications only open to South African Citizens / Permanent Residents.\n \nJob description\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for, but not be limited to:\n         Monitor and update raise drilling schedules on MS Projects\n         Assist the Project Manager with export / import administration of plant and equipment in line with permit requirements within timelines\n         Draft commercial letters as required per contract\n         Verify that project timelines are met as per CCS\n         Monitor commercial risks within required timelines\n         Interpret engineering drawings and mine layouts and assist with the execution thereof\n         Maintain and update the drawing register for all projects\n         Maintain and update the client communication register for all projects\n         Update and track contract amendments\n         Update and maintain project handover register\n         Understand the commercial and legal aspects of all projects\n         Effective self-management in alignment with M&RC\u2019s values\n \nMinimum requirements\nSuitable candidates must possess the following minimum qualifications and skills:\n         Grade 12 or NQF 4 equivalent\n         Project Management Degree / Advanced Project Management Diploma NQF 6 or similar\n         COMSOC 1 & 2 (advantageous)\n         Proficient in Microsoft Office [MS Projects [essential], PowerPoint, Word and Excel]\n         Administrative competence\n         Ability to plan, organise, schedule and coordinate activities\n         Ability to work under limited supervision\n         Valid Driver\u2019s License and passport\n         Good English written and verbal communication skills\nSuitable candidates must have the following work experience:\n         Minimum 5 years of experience in project coordination and planning in a mining environment\n         Basic knowledge of NEC, FIDIC and bespoke contract laws\n         Experience in orepass rehabilitation and underground construction\n         Proficient and experienced in technical / commercial drafting of letters\n         Experience interpreting engineering drawings and underground mining plans\nAll appointments will be done in line with our employment equity strategy.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your application unsuccessful.\n \nAPPLY",
                "EPC CONSTRUCTION MANAGER - OPTIPOWER VARIOUS PROJECTS\nListing reference: mr_001556\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 21 March 2024\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Electricity, Energy & Water Supply\nJob category: Energy and Power Engineering\nLocation: South Africa\nContract: Fixed Term Contract\nRemuneration: Market Related\n \nIntroduction\nThe EPC Construction Manager (\u201cEPC CM\u201d) is responsible for overseeing all on-site activities relating to the construction of Utility-scale Solar PV Projects throughout the construction phase, from Notice to Proceed (\u201cNTP\u201d) to Commercial Operation Date (\u201cCOD\u201d) and Power Plant Hand-Over. The EPC CM is the on-site representative of the EPC Contractor (\u201cContractor\u201d) and is the main point of contact for all subcontractors, consultants and third parties performing activities on the project site (\u201cSite\u201d). The EPC CM will liaise with all representatives of the Client (\u201cEmployer\u201d) based on Site. The Employer\u2019s Representatives include, but is not limited to, the Employer\u2019s Construction Manager, the Employer\u2019s Engineer, the Owners\u2019 Engineer (\u201cOE\u201d), the Lenders Technical Advisor (\u201cLTA\u201d), the Employer\u2019s Health & Safety Agent, the Environmental Control Officer (ECO\u201d), when applicable, or any other third parties and / or consultants based on Site, appointed by the Employer. The EPC CM\u2019s primary role is to oversee the execution of the construction activities on Site. However, the EPC CM will also be responsible for overseeing all other non-construction related Site activities within the perimeter of the Site. These include, but are not limited to, Site Security & Access Control, activities relating to Health & Safety, Site Facilities and Infrastructure, Site Resources and Consumables (Fuel, Potable Water, etc.) or any other activities performed on Site to ensure the successful completion of the Solar PV Plant. The EPC CM must ensure all subcontractors and other service providers fulfil their contractual obligations specifically in terms of safety, quality, schedule and budget, in terms of their respective Scope of Works, Subcontractor Agreements and Service Level Agreements (SLAs), when and if applicable, as related to the Site activities. All construction managers appointed by the respective subcontractors and all other representatives appointed by other service providers to manage their personnel on Site will report to the EPC CM. As the Contractor\u2019s legally appointed Construction Manager in terms of Section 8.1 of the Construction Regulations of the Occupational Health and Safety Act (\u201cOHS Act\u201d), the EPC CM must ensure full compliance pursuant to the OHS Act by all on Site, including the Employer\u2019s representatives based on Site, or any other visitors visiting the Site. The EPC CM reports to and works closely with the EPC Project Manager (\u201cEPC PM\u201d), to ensure the Contractor fulfils all its contractual obligations in terms of the EPC Contract, by executing the Project on time, to the desired quality in a safe and environmentally responsible manner.\n \nJob description\nKey Performance Indicators:\nHealth & Safety Management \u2013 Zero Fatalities and Zero Lost Time Injuries (LTIs). Monthly Attendance of Health & Safety Site Meetings. Full compliance to the OHS Act.\nWaste & Environmental Management \u2013 Full implementation of Waste Management Plan. Full compliance to the National Environmental Management Act (\u201cNEMA\u201d) and NEM: Waste Act. Full compliance to the Environmental Management Programme (\u201cEMPr\u201d) as included in the Environmental Authorisation (\u201cEA\u201d). Implement and maintain high Housekeeping Standards and ensure the Site remains clean and tidy at all times.\nSite Management & Subcontractor Management \u2013 Identify construction risks and possible bottlenecks and proactively align efforts of the various disciplines and respective subcontractor Scope of Works to ensure efficiencies and a high productivity rate.\nQuality Control & Inspection \u2013 Implement the Quality Control Plan. Ensure inspections of the Works when required and holding points signed-off. Ensure Inspection Sheets and Test Reports are up to date and stored in the Project Data Room as per the Document Control Procedure. Encourage the First Time Right (\u201cFTR\u201d) principal to avoid costly and time-consuming reworks.\nMonitoring & Reporting \u2013 Daily monitoring of all Site activities and timeous submission of Key Project Progress Indicators and other reports, as required by and agreed with the EPC PM.\nTime & Cost Management \u2013 Ensure Construction activities are completed on time as per the Project Programme (Schedule) and within budget, or as per pre-approved (by the EPC PM), variations when applicable.\nConstruction Drawings, Designs & Document Control \u2013 Ensure strict adherence to the Document Control procedure by all EPC personnel and subcontractors on Site.\nStakeholder Engagement & Customer Satisfaction \u2013 Build professional relationships with subcontractors, organised labour and the Employer\u2019s representatives working on Site.\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nTake full ownership of the Solar PV Project Construction Site from NTP to COD and Power Plant Hand-Over.\nServe as the Contractor\u2019s primary on-site representative.\nTake full responsibility of Health & Safety on Site as the Construction Manager legally appointed in terms of Section 8.1 of the Construction Regulations of the Occupational Health and Safety Act (\u201cOHS Act\u201d).\nEnsure the Contractor fulfil its\u2019 contractual obligation in terms of the lump sum fixed price EPC Contract with respect to all Site activities.\nClosely collaborate with the EPC team on Site to ensure project success.\nKeep a Construction Site Daily Dairy and conduct daily Site Meetings with the EPC team and subcontractor representatives and / or construction managers to coordinate the various Site activities of the respective subcontractors. \nContinuously monitor the construction activities and progress, and provide daily reports and updates to the EPC PM on the construction progress, including quality and safety metrics, in the required format.\nProvide regular updates specific to the construction activities to management and external partners (only when contractually required to do so).\nInterface with the Utility and project Off-Takers on Site and only with respect to on-Site activities.\nEnsure the Construction Site Safety File is up to date and immediately address any shortcoming or outstanding information and / or liaise with the EPC PM to resolve issues.\nCoordinate the project Commissioning, Performance Testing and Closeout activities, with support from the Contractor\u2019s appointed Commissioning Engineer and support staff.\nCoordinate the training of the Employer\u2019s Operations and Maintenance (\u201cO&M\u201d) team during Hot Commission until COD with support from the Contractor\u2019s O&M internal personnel and / or external consultants.\nMonitor the Contractor and respective subcontractors\u2019 compliance with their respective contracts and / or SLAs, specifically in terms of Quality, Safety, Schedule and Budget and related to on Site activities.\nConduct daily site audits, specifically but not limited to, construction activities on the Critical Path, in coordination with Quality Control Lead, Health & Safety Lead and EPC PM and identify possible risks and / or bottlenecks to be addressed and resolved.\n \nAttributes:\nThorough knowledge of Health and Safety procedures and legislation pertaining to Construction Site activities and zero tolerance towards non-compliance to the Occupational Health and Safety Act and Construction Regulations.\nGood communicative and interpersonal skills.         \nOutput, performance and service driven.\nResilience and problem-solving skills.\nQuality and safety conscious.\nExcellent Planning Skills.\nAbility to make decisions under pressure.\nGood Sound commercial awareness.\nGood numerical and computer skills.\nLeadership skills and the ability to motivate team\n \nMinimum requirements\nQualifications:\nBTech in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering\nSACPCMP Certification advantageous\nConstruction Regulations Certificate\nOHS Act Certificate\nLegal Liability Certificate\nHIRA Certificate\nPlanned task observations Certificate\n \nSkills & Experience \nHave previously performed the above duties and responsibilities for Utility-Scale Solar PV Projects.\nHave previous experience in lump sum fixed price EPC Contracts for the Solar PV Projects.\nPreference: Experience on projects over 100MWp.\nSubstation and transmission line construction and commissioning experience.\nPhysically fit to work at the Construction Site full-time during the construction phase of the Project.\nExpertise in EPC Construction Processes and Procedures.\nAbility to work with Microsoft Office Software.\n \nAll appointments will be filled in line with our employment equity plan.\n \nDisclaimer\nThe Recruiter may amend, delete or expire jobs at any time without notification.\nMurray & Roberts reserves the right not to proceed with filling the position.\nAn application will not in itself entitle the applicant to an interview.\nIf you do not receive any feedback on your application within 4 weeks from the closing date, please consider your application unsuccessful\n \nAPPLY"
