                " \n \nENGINEERING SUPERINTENDENT\n \nJob highlights\nGlencore Coal SA\nWitbank, Mpumalanga, South Africa\niMpunzi Complex\nJob IDIMP MM 2024/01\nClosing date21/03/2024\n \nAPPLY\n \nThe incumbent in this role will be responsible for overseeing the delivery and execution of the maintenance plan in areas of responsibility, focusing on safety the selection, development, support and optimal utilization of people and adherence to systems and procedures.\n \n Key Responsibilities\nImplementing and managing maintenance plans for areas of responsibility and communicating monthly and weekly maintenance targets; and monitoring and offering technical guidance to Supervisors to ensure the safe delivery of targets.\nManaging resource capability, allocation, utilisation and driving the delivery of targets and equipment availability.\nMeasuring the performance of Foremen, providing guidance and coaching through the implementation of good standards and best practice.\nEnsuring adherence to Legislation, Policies, Procedures, Standards and Operating Procedures in areas of responsibility.\nEngaging relevant stakeholders to solve operational problems in areas of responsibility as necessary.\nEnsuring that daily performance monitoring and interventions are in place to support and correct performance in areas of responsibility.\n \n Minimum Qualifications and experience\nN6 Certificate with engineering subjects and valid Trade Certificate (Diesel Mechanic) and a minimum of 3 years\u2019 experience as an Engineering Supervisor; OR\nA relevant degree and completion of the Graduate Development Programme.\nDragline, Drill, Electrical Reticulation, LDV & MDV experience.\n \nBehaviour Competencies:\nAbility to take the lead, set objectives, sequence processes/initiatives/projects and organise resources to manage risk and achieve objectives.\nHas the courage to question long standing assumptions and communicate a different perspective.\nAbility to inspire and foster commitment, pride and trust amongst team members by taking a democratic approach, seeking and valuing contributions and encouraging collaboration.\nAbility to take decisive action and assume responsibility for making difficult decisions that affect people and business performance.\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nIT \u2013 SITE SUPPORT SPECIALIST\nJob highlights\nGlencore Coal SA\nRustenburg, North West, South Africa\nShared Services\nJob IDSS MM 2024/01\nClosing date21/03/2024\n \nAPPLY\n \nThe incumbent in this role is responsible for managing and guiding resources required for first-level IT support, rolling out the support strategy and ensuring that high quality support services are provided to support business needs.\n \n Key Responsibilities\nManaging site IT infrastructure.\nRegistering incidents, escalating, trend and root cause analysis and problem resolution.\nMaintaining IT tasks, installing, configuring and trouble shooting of hardware and software.\nManaging IT continuity.\nFacilitating and governing the IT Projects on site.\nEnsuring the IT Services address the changing business needs.\nDeveloping and maintaining training plans for the site IT Teams as well as encouraging continuous learning.\nEnsuring ongoing site compliance to Glencore IT policies, procedures and legislation.\n \n Minimum Qualifications\nRelevant Degree.\n \nMinimum Experience\nMinimum 5 years\u2019 experience in the IT environment.\nUnderstanding and working knowledge of IT Support Delivery.\n \nBehaviour Competencies:\nAbility to take decisive action and assume responsibility for making difficult decisions that affect people and business performance.\nAbility to create shared meaning by clearly and confidently communicating the relevant information to a decision or task, in a verbal format.\nAbility to inspire and foster commitment, pride and trust amongst team members by taking a democratic approach, seeking and valuing contributions and encouraging collaboration.\nAbility to treat diverse groups of people with respect and to effectively employ this diversity to the advantage of the Company.\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "MINING ENGINEER: MEDIUM-TERM PLANNING\nJob highlights\nGlencore Coal SA\nWitbank, Mpumalanga, South Africa\nTweefontein Complex\nJob ID TWF MM 2024/01\nClosing date 21/03/2024\n \nAPPLY\n \nThe incumbent in the role is responsible for supporting the Complex by ensuring optimal exploitation of coal reserves and assisting in meeting operational and strategic business objectives.\n \nKey Responsibilities:\nConducting medium-term planning activities for the opencast operations.\nSupporting the production process to achieve planned targets.\nFulfilling daily, weekly, monthly and quarterly reporting duties.\nSupporting the preparation of reserves and parameters.\nConducting viability studies.\n \nMinimum Qualifications:\nA relevant degree in Mining Engineering.\nA Surface Blasting Certificate for Coal Mines.\nA Mine Managers\u2019 Certificate of Competency or Glencore internal Law Examination will be an added advantage.\n \nMinimum Experience:\nMinimum 2 years\u2019 experience in an Opencast Production environment at a Production Superintendent level.\nTechnical Mine Planning experience in an opencast environment.\nProficiency in Microsoft Office, Mine Design and Scheduling software.\n \nBehavioural Competencies:\nAbility to take the lead, set objectives, sequence processes/initiatives/projects and organize resources to manage risk and achieve objectives.\nAbility to drill into the detail of issues to determine root cause whilst considering urgency, importance, risk and reward factors.\nAbility to carefully and objectively analyse and evaluate information to inform decisions and key actions.\nAbility to work consistently hard to achieve deliverables and honour commitments made.\nAbility to maintain high levels of individual and team performance by driving the achievement of goals, targets and financial objectives.\n \nAPPLY",
                "HUMAN RESOURCES MANAGER\nJob highlights\nHuman Resources Manager\nSteelpoort\nManagement\nJob ID HRM/LION/032024\nClosing date 20/03/2024\n \nAPPLY\n \nHuman Resources Manager\nOffering advice and guidance to employees, supervisors and Management which includes but is not limited to HR, Employee Relations and HRD-related matters. \n\nServing as a link between Management and employees. \nAdvising managers on legal requirements, such as employment equity, the Labour Relations Act, basic conditions of employment and skills development.\nEnsuring adherence to and effective implementation of company policies and procedures. \nEnsuring the implementation of fundamental HR practices such as recruitment, training and development, developing job specifications/profiles, performance management and succession planning.\nPromoting sound employee relations and consultation with unions.\nManaging all administrative functions.\nAnalysing the performance of the Human Resource function and initiating continuous improvement initiatives in line with best practices.\nCompiling information and reports related to projects and programmes of the HR Department.\nManaging services like the canteen, change rooms, employee transport\n \nAPPLY"
