                " \n \n3P LOGISTICS FACILITATOR\nJob ID: R-85010\nCategory: Supply Chain\nLocation: Boksburg, Gauteng\nDate posted: 03/05/2024\n \nABOUT UNILEVER\nWith 3.4 billion people in over 190 countries using our products every day, Unilever is a business that makes a real impact on the world. Work on brands that are loved and improve the lives of our consumers and the communities around us. We are driven by our purpose: to make sustainable living commonplace, and it is our belief that doing business the right way drives superior performance. At the heart of what we do is our people \u2013 we believe that when our people work with purpose, we will create a better business and a better world. \n\nAt Unilever, your career will be a unique journey, grounded in our inclusive, collaborative, and flexible working environment. We don\u2019t believe in the \u2018one size fits all\u2019 approach and instead we will equip you with the tools you need to shape your own future.\n \nJOB PURPOSE\nUnilever is the place where you can bring your purpose to life with the work that you do \u2013 creating a better business and a better world.  If you are passionate about logistics management then this role is just for you!\nThe Purpose of the 3P Logistics Facilitator is to be responsible for Unilever RPM & FG materials mainly but not limited at 3P. This includes SAP maintenance and physical stock accountability.\n \nWHAT WILL YOUR MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES BE\nStock Capture, reconciliation & movement in SAP\nReceipt, capture and move RM/PM received at 3P into SAP\nSystem movements (back flushing) for all raw & packaging material at the end of every production run \u2013 drive physical movement and ensure system transfer is done\nReceive and process Delivery Notes for payment and update DN details accordingly on system.\nAccurately enter data into corresponding fields within various software programs\nIdentify and correct data entry errors using appropriate quality control methods\nFacilitate movement of FG to UL Warehouses- Transport booking and SAP transactions (Printing and sticking of pallet labels)\nDaily reporting to reconcile overall stock receipts, dispatch, clearing bins, clearing SIT (confirm and validate)\nAssisting 3P with UL invoicing- correct documentation quoted\nCo-ordinate weekly stock count with 3P \u2013 writing on and writing off stock\nInvestigation and report of stock losses post the stock count - Provisions\nChecking and correcting S/LOC \u2013 RPM and FG\nRM/PM and FG \u2013 Write ons and Write offs\nRM/PM movement between plants\nAttendance and input into monthly/quarterly UL and operational review\nPerforms any other adhoc reasonable instruction requested by line manager from time to time\nInvoice Queries  - (e.g. DCIW\u2019s)\nOff-Site counts \u2013 Bi-annually\nFrequent engagement with supply Chain Finance on Accruals raised for LAB.\nEnsuring smooth FG transfer between BBG and BBDC.\n \nKey Inputs\nMust be able to network within a data team and interact with Managers across the business.\nDeliver optimum results through relationship building with suppliers to help maximize stock efficiency.\nDay to day contact and relationship with Site Material planner & Procurement.\nDrive planning through insights and experience\nReport and analyse Key Performance Indicators, implementing continuous improvement activities around these.\nDrive tracking and score card updates via weekly reporting and accountability standards\nUltimately, a successful data entry operator will be responsible for maintaining accurate, up-to-date and useable information in our systems.\n \nWHAT YOU NEED TO SUCCEED\nExperiences & Qualifications\nGrade 12/ Matric\nBachelor\u2019s Degree/National Diploma in Logistics / Warehouse /Operations Management/ Industrial Engineering/ Finance will be an advantage.\n2-3 years\u2019 working experience in Production, Logistics, Warehouse, FMCG/ Manufacturing\nLiaise and negotiate with suppliers/ third parties, contractors and manufacturers\nUnderstand raw materials, processing, making and packaging\nWorking knowledge and experience in production, supply chain, and planning\nHave excellent supervisory, coordination, organization, planning\nManage multiple stakeholders and numerous improvement projects \nSubject matter expert, provide guidance and support and hold others accountable\nSAP, Outlook, Excel, Word, working knowledge\n \nSkills\nAgile delivery\nChange management\nData driven decision making\nLean Techniques\n \nLeadership\nYou are energized by delivering fantastic results. You are an example to others \u2013 both your results and your resilience. You are constantly on the lookout for better ways to do things, engaging and collaborating with others along the way.\nAs an individual you are the one responsible for your own wellbeing and delivering high standards of work. You must also focus on the Consumer and what they need. You are humble and have your head up, looking around to interpret evidence and data smartly, spot issues and opportunities to make things better.\nCritical SOL (Standards of Leadership) Behaviors\nPASSION FOR HIGH PERFORMANCE: Takes personal responsibility and accountability for execution and results. Has an owner\u2019s mindset, using data and insight to make decisions.\nPERSONAL MASTERY: Sets high standards for themselves. Actively builds own wellbeing and resilience.\nCONSUMER LOVE: Whatever their role, always looks for better ways to serve consumers. Invests time inside and outside to understand the needs of consumers.\nPURPOSE & SERVICE: Has humility, understanding that leadership is service to others, inside and outside Unilever.\nAGILITY: Explores the world around them, continually learning and developing their skills.\n \nUnilever embraces diversity and encourages applicants from all walks of life! This means giving full and fair consideration to all applicants and continuing development of all employees regardless of age, disability, gender reassignment, race, religion or belief, sex, sexual orientation, marriage and civil partnership, and pregnancy and maternity. \nUnilever is an organisation committed to equity, inclusion and diversity to drive our business results and create a better future, every day, for our diverse employees, global consumers, partners, and communities. We believe a diverse workforce allows us to match our growth ambitions and drive inclusion across the business. At Unilever we are interested in every individual bringing their \u2018Whole Self\u2019 to work and this includes you! Thus if you require any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at the time of your application so that we can support you through your recruitment journey.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                "ASSISTANT PROCUREMENT MANAGER - CAPEX & MRO\nJob ID: R-84680\nCategory: Supply Chain\nLocation: Sandhurst, Gauteng\nDate posted: 03/03/2024\n \nAssistant Procurement Manager \u2013 CAPEX/MRO (South Africa)\n \nMAIN JOB PURPOSE:\nSupport Procurement Manager with delivering key targets related to Cost and Cash, Quality and Service, Innovation and Sustainable Living.\n \nKEY ACCOUNTABILITIES:\nSupport Procurement Manager in developing and executing supplier strategy for CAPEX/MRO (Maintenance and Repairs Operations) portfolio, which has annual spend of circa, 40mil EURO for 6 manufacturing sites and 2 warehouses in South Africa.\nAssess supply market and adapt strategy according to market conditions.\nAssess supplier capability and suitability through regular site visits and reporting back on findings.\nDevelop and improve supplier cost models to drive increase in transparency of cost drivers\nUnlock cash and cost value through setting up and execution of benchmarking, RFQs, E-tenders. Support delivery of savings and creditor extension programme for portfolio\nSupport and occasionally lead supplier negotiations\nProvide market intelligence to portfolio manager and business leaders to assist in strategic decision making.\nConnect with site engineering and regional engineering teams and other business partners as well as with suppliers, to understand future technology and capability roadmap that supports value delivery and USLP.\nAllocate new services to suppliers to deliver best cost/service/quality in line with supply strategy.\nLead on-boarding of new suppliers by driving full quality and responsible sourcing compliance\nEnsure 100% contractual compliance through signing of Unilever Purchasing Agreements and Commercial Term Contracts as well as Special Term Contracts\nAgree annual budgets with suppliers. Implement into new CTC. Communicate/process changes in pricing as required\nRegularly connect with global counterparts to ensure the Africa portfolio is link with the global strategy.\nSuccessful implement global strategic plans in Africa\nManage relationships with Supply chain and other business partners, to leverage and land strategic plans.\nGood understanding of the portfolio cost models as well as the indices link to the material types.\nProfessional Skills:\nProcurement Insights and Analysis: Understand portfolio strategies and procurement requirements; Industry, global Strategy & Insights teams, economic, competition and supplier insights.\nProcurement Strategy Formulation: Developing services supply strategy; Develop supplier strategies; Integrating procurement strategy into the business.\nProcurement Strategy Execution and Performance Management: Competitive bidding and tendering; Supplier negotiation; Supplier qualification and on-boarding; Contractual supplier engagement; Supplier performance measurement and management\nPartnering with Suppliers to Win: Attract, select, manage and motivate partners; Identifying value creating opportunities.\nDriving Sustainability, Supplier Diversity and Digitalization through Procurement: Services Supply Chain analysis and risk assessment; Evidence-based measurement for sustainability\n \nSKILLS/EXPERIENCE:\n3-5 years\u2019 experience in Procurement, Supply Management or Finance\nExperience on large-scale change management projects\nExperience in CAPEX/MRO (Maintenance, Repairs and Operations) portfolio or FMCG\n \nUnilever is an organisation committed to equity, inclusion and diversity to drive our business results and create a better future, every day, for our diverse employees, global consumers, partners, and communities. We believe a diverse workforce allows us to match our growth ambitions and drive inclusion across the business. At Unilever we are interested in every individual bringing their \u2018Whole Self\u2019 to work and this includes you! Thus if you require any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at the time of your application so that we can support you through your recruitment journey.\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "ASSISTANT PROCUREMENT MANAGER\nJob ID: R-84565\nCategory: Supply Chain\nLocation: La Lucia, KwaZulu-Natal\nDate posted: 02/29/2024\n \nUnilever is currently hiring for : Assistant Procurement Manager\nFunction: Supply chain>Procurement\nLocation: Unilever La Lucia Ridge Office\nTerms & Conditions: Full time\n \nJOB PURPOSE\nUnilever is the place where you can bring your purpose to life with the work that you do \u2013 creating a better business and a better world.  If you are Support Procurement Manager with delivering key targets related to Cost and Cash, Quality and Service, Innovation and Sustainable Living then this role is just for you!\n \nWHAT WILL YOUR MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES BE\n\n\u2022Support Procurement Manager in developing and executing supplier strategy for portfolio\n\u2022Assess supply market and adapt strategy according to market conditions\n\u2022Assess supplier capability and suitability through regular site visits and reporting back on findings\n\u2022Develop and improve supplier cost models to drive increase in transparency of cost drivers\n\u2022Unlock cash and cost value through setting up and execution of benchmarking, RFQs, E-tenders. Support delivery of savings and creditor extension programme for portfolio\n\u2022Support and occasionally lead supplier negotiations\n\u2022Track global feedstock and forex movements and translate into price forecasts required regularly by business\n\u2022Provide market intelligence to PM and business leaders to assist in strategic decision making\n\u2022Support innovation by identifying capable suppliers to deliver required specifications of materials\n\u2022Connect with RD business partners to understand future supplier technology and capability roadmap that supports value delivery and USLP. Assist in delivering roadmap\n\u2022Allocate new materials to suppliers to deliver best cost/service/quality in line with supply strategy\n\u2022Lead on-boarding of new suppliers by driving full quality and responsible sourcing compliance\n\u2022Ensure 100% contractual compliance through signing of Unilever Purchasing Agreements and Commercial Term Contracts as well as Special Term Contracts\n\u2022Agree quarterly and annual material prices with suppliers. Implement into new CTC. Submit prices to proc ops colleagues for contract upload\n\u2022Regularly connect with procurement operations and category colleagues to understand GM, service, quality, capacity, WC hot spots. Engage suppliers and adapt strategy to drive improvement in hot-spot areas\n \nExperiences & Qualifications\nAt 3-5 years\u2019 experience in Procurement or Supply Management\nExperience on large-scale change management projects\nExperience in relevant portfolio\n \nUnilever is an organisation committed to equity, inclusion and diversity to drive our business results and create a better future, every day, for our diverse employees, global consumers, partners, and communities. We believe a diverse workforce allows us to match our growth ambitions and drive inclusion across the business. At Unilever we are interested in every individual bringing their \u2018Whole Self\u2019 to work and this includes you! Thus if you require any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at the time of your application so that we can support you through your recruitment journey.\n \nAPPLY NOW"
