                " \n \nPAYROLL AND HR ADMINISTRATOR AT CATER CHAIN FOOD SERVICES\nUndisclosed\nPermanent Intermediate position\nCity Deep\nJob 2554991\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nEnsure that all the appropriate HR procedures are followed and correct paper trail is completed correctly\nFollow induction and orientation whereby new employees have been employed.\nCompile and complete necessary HR related documents ie. AOD's, confirmation of employment\nEnsure that all HR and T&A paperwork has been signed off correctly\nEnsure that payroll receive all relevant paperwork and T&A data in a timeous manner\nAssistance in following the process whereby employees have been terminated and ensure that all the appropriate procedures are followed and correct paper trail is completed.\nFilling and archiving\nAssist with training and development\nHR Administration\nRecruitment\nAssist with checking service provider invoices to tie up with costing reports\nAssist with employment equity\nDo payroll for all staff\n \nDesired Skills:\nSage\nHR Administration\nOrganized\nTime Management\n \nDesired Work Experience:\n1 to 2 years FMCG\n2 to 5 years Human Resources\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nDiploma\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nHEALTH AND SAFETY COORDINATOR AT CATER CHAIN FOOD SERVICES\nUndisclosed\nPermanent Intermediate position\nCity Deep\nJob 2554561\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nAdvises management on safety compliance concerns and preventative actions.\nPlans and implements training for employees in work site safety practices.\nMaintains safety files and records\nPerforms safety surveys and inspections, prepares written reports of findings and recommendations for corrective or preventive measures where indicated and follows up to ensure measures have been implemented.\nConducts post-accident investigation and prepares report identifying possible accident causes and hazards for use by company personnel and senior management.\nSets up and conducts training.\nWorks to development, evaluation and upgrading of safety systems\nInterpret, translate and provide expect advise & guidance to line management on health and safety statutory and regulatory requirements\nManage and review of the Health and Safety plans\nDeliver general EHS training on site, drive EHS training program of the company with HR and managers to comply with statutory- requirements\nCo-ordinate the testing and drills of contingency plans for the business to ensure readiness for emergencies\nCoordinate incident reporting, recording and investigations according to OSH Act and ensure root cause are identified and controls implemented ro prevent recurrence.\nCoordinating the return of injured workers into workplace\nConducting and coordinating of Hazard identification, risk assessment programs and ensure effective controls are implemented and working.\nBachelors Degree in environmental health, safety\nMinimum five years experience working in manufacturing or FMCG industry\nMeat experience (advantageous)\n \nDesired Skills:\nOHSAS 18001\nHSE Management Systems\nH&S Management\nHealth & Safety\nOccupational hygiene\nEnvironmental Management Systems\n \nDesired Work Experience:\n2 to 5 years FMCG\n2 to 5 years Health, Safety & Environment\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nDiploma\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nFITTER (6MONTHS FTC) AT CATER CHAIN FOOD SERVICES\nContract Intermediate position\nCity Deep\nJob 2554016\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nPlan and manage all planned maintenance, preventative schedules, work requests and break downs.\nDetermine material, equipment, and supplies to be used and ensure that these are ordered and available at the work site.\nHelp plan and manage weekend mechanical maintenance tasks and projects.\nUse planned maintenance schedules to coordinate daily activities of maintance assistants and implement operational asset productivity and care through the planned maintenance strategy by noting and driving the resolution of maintenance issues.\nMonitor, measure and report on engineering related down-time and general issues.\nFault find on mechanical equipment to ascertain and repair faults to ensure production can continue.\nAttend to and resource mechanical breakdowns timeously in order to minimise production downtime.\nFitting, fabricating, and assembling of structural components on various mechanical systems\nRepair and service machinery\nAble to safely use hand and power tools (welding, cutting, drilling)\nKeep record of all maintenance work done\nInitiate RCI's (Root Cause Analysis) and proper problem-solving investigations fix problem\nadhering to all safety rules and regulations\nTrade Test Certificate\nDrivers licence\nWireman's License (Optional)\n \nDesired Skills:\nHand Tools\nWoodworking\nWelding\nFittings\nHydraulic Assembly\n \nDesired Work Experience:\n2 to 5 years FMCG\n2 to 5 years Artisan\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nCertificate\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                "TEAM LEADER: ROUTE OPTIMISATION AT FAMOUS BRANDS\nPermanent Senior position\nMidrand\nJob 2552809\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nThe core functional areas of this role are to manage, support and link internal distribution centre to drive optimised routes through the most efficient distribution method to retain customer satisfaction and deliver on improved utilisation of all resources.\nEnforce compliance within the department to all Internal Policies, SOP, and the Company Code of Conduct\nAnalyse reports and extract key actions for execution\nManage routing and delivery schedule for national customer base across secondary and retail execution.\nMeasure Transportation spend and optimization network cross all Distribution methods.\nDetermine the correct routing by balancing the workload across the different route type\nUtilize planning software (Plato) ensuring Data Base remains up to date with the correct parameter to optimise route scheduling\nMeasuring and monitor the Utilisation of all resources at the best possible capacity with no impact on customer service or operational demand, and within all legal requirements.\nCompile and evaluate planning reports for the DC, based on their execution performance to ensure compliance and improvement in KPI's\nCommunicate clearly and concisely with all DC and internal departments the expectations of route planning to continuously drive improvement on service levels and finance.\nWork with Operations and Distribution leaders to forecast labour and resource requirements on a day-to-day basis\nRecognize departmental and organizational needs and develop action plans to help meet those needs\nIdentify delivery capability within each of the DC and develop action plans to achieve the desired outcomes and benefits for each site\nProvide weekly consolidated communication to Group LOG Management and DC leaders on PVA achievements\nEnsure customer NDD's alignments within\nCustomer operating days and time windows\nWarehouse activity smoothing\nDIS shift configurations within the legal requirements\nOverall resource capacity\nEnsure productivity and cost KPIs are monitored and communicated, supported with Budget and the PVA\nCost per KM, Cost per Trip, Cost per Case\nCases per KM, Cases per Trip, Cases per Stop\nDrive the reduction planned over time within the organization and productivity within the execution platform\nReporting on excessive KM/Hours/trips executed by the operational team.\nEnsure the planning platform and Data bases is link to the Control Tower for accurate data and group performance\n \nDesired Skills:\nExecution systems / Live Tracking (Trackmatic)\nPlanning tool (Opsi Products preferably PLATO)\n \nDesired Work Experience:\n2 to 5 years Team Leader & Supervisor\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nDiploma\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n ",
                "PRODUCTION INTERN AT CATER CHAIN FOOD SERVICES\nInternship position\nCity Deep\nJob 2551372\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nIdentifying, prioritizing, analyzing, and eliminating losses and inefficiencies\nCreating learning programs and coaching and training technicians\nCreating and improving standards, tools, and processes to enable us to achieve the performance targets for the production line Understanding and working with state-of-the-art robotics and automated equipment\nHave less than 2 years relevant work experience\nIndustrial Engineering / Production Degree/Diploma\n \nDesired Skills:\nProblem Solving\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nDiploma\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "BRAND MANAGER - FUN DINING AT FAMOUS BRANDS\nPermanent Management position\nMidrand\nJob 2551335\nAPPLY NOW\n \nABOUT THE POSITION\nAssist in development of the annual brand strategy and Marketing plan for respective brands.\nPlan and execute national marketing activities above and below the line in relation to the approved Marketing plan and promotions calendar.\nSeek new opportunities to deliver growth against the brand plan and/or improve the [URL Removed] and manage the media plan.\nEnsuring that expenditure and brand objectives are delivered.\nDevelop clear briefs and manage all advertising agencies, strategic alliance partners and suppliers on advertising and promotional campaigns.\nEnsure all marketing collateral delivers on the brand CI in conjunction with the relevant agencies.\nBrief all bimonthly Menu briefs and product development briefs to New Product Manager\nEnsure all Purchase orders are issued, and payments made to all service providers monthly.\nMonthly reporting and explanations on Marketing Fund spend.\nManage the brand CRM program, encouraging customer retention and customer loyalty. This includes segmenting the database, developing CRM campaigns and analysing and producing monthly reports on the growth of the database and success of campaigns.\nDrive database acquisition through acquisition campaigns and technology\nAssist in management of public relations and brand sponsorships.\nAssist in the development of a two-year innovation pipeline to meet brand objectives.\nProvide forecasts for promotions and new products to minimize write off costs.\nDrive menu optimisation with regards to pricing strategy and menu mix to achieve targeted average GPs and deliver value to the brand's customer base.\nManage and co-ordinate national menu rollouts.\nManage branding and design of all consumer touch points (including signage, uniforms, packaging, restaurant look and feel, website etc.) to ensure they align with brand CI.\nAssist in delivering on the brand's digital and technology plan and manage the brand's digital and social media activities.\nUtilise consumer research and consumer feedback data (Yext) to gain consumer insights that drive decisions and rituals.\nAnalyse sales data and report on the performance of promotions and products\nEvaluate competitor pricing and report on a quarterly basis.\nManage the marketing budget to ensure nil [URL Removed] and optimize 3rd party delivery platforms\n \nDesired Skills:\nExcellent interpersonal\nwritten & presentation skills -\nHighly enumerate & computer literate -\nMinimum Intermediate to advanced\nExcel\nPowerPoint and Outlook skills -\nStrong communications skills and writing skills -\nProactive\ninnovative thinker\nability to implement with excellence and accuracy -\nMulti-task orientated -\nAbility to work well under pressure -\nDeadline driven -\nAttention to detail -\nCreative thinking -\nProblem solver and analytical thinking ability -\nAbility to adapt to a rapidly changing environment -\nHigh degree of brand ownership and accountability -\nAbility to work well in a team orientated environment -\nQuick learning ability\n \nDesired Work Experience:\n2 to 5 years Restaurant & Bar\n5 to 10 years Brand Management\n \nDesired Qualification Level:\nDegree\n \nAbout The Employer:\nUnder the guidance and support of the Marketing Manager, effectively manage all elements of the brand marketing mix in order to ensure that the brand continues to grow\n \nAPPLY NOW"
