                "DC GENERAL MANAGER\nat takealot.com\nKwaZulu Natal\n\ntakealot.com, a leading South African online retailer, is looking for a highly talented DC General Manager to join our Supply Chain team in KZN DC.\nThe incumbent will manage the overall risk and compliance, including Safety, Health and Environment (SHE) of the Takealot Operations division, in the pursuit of a zero loss culture in the Group, with innovation and value add.\nWe are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hardworking people with integrity to join us.  We offer a market related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won\u2019t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.\nThis position reports to:  Head of Operations\nStandard working hours: Monday to Friday 08:00 \u2013 17:00, however overtime may be required during peak periods and promotions\n \nPurpose of position: Responsible for managing and directing all operation activities within the distribution center, covering above 50,000 square meters and employing over 500 staff members. A leader of change, providing overall leadership and management in operational areas such as: Operational efficiency, continuous improvement, driving performance and optimally satisfying customer orders.\n \nYour responsibilities will include:\nOverall management and coordination of all DC activities (inbound, outbound, returns, inventory management, Risk and facility management)\nDrive operational efficiency and excellence\nImplement operational best practices\nProvide staff leadership and direction\nEnsuring DC adheres to company policy and administer practices in fair and equitable manner.\nManaging budget and controlling expenses.\nRecommending policies and programs, which guide the organization in maintaining and improving its competitive position and the profitability of the operation.\nEnsures appropriate staffing levels by effectively forecasting resources needed to meet service, financial and operational requirements.\nDevelops annual operating budgets in support of the company's financial goals and responsible for P&L management. Complete cost justification and determine ROI.\nControls cost through process improvement initiatives, productivity of personnel, efficient utilization of space and protection of stored materials. Ensures protection and accuracy of inventory by adhering to all inventory control processes and procedures.\nDemonstrate the ability to understand and meet the needs of customers; both internal and external.\nCommunicate and articulate to staff what the vision for the organization looks like and communicating clear strategies to move toward that vision.\nProvide team members with opportunities to develop new skills, carry out challenging assignments, and accept new responsibilities while ensuring a talent base necessary to meet organizational needs.\nSets / clarifies requirements and expectations for DC Managers. \nMeasures performance, provides feedback, and hold DC Managers accountable for their performance and the performance of their departments. \nTakes proactive steps to ensure that best practices are shared across all departments & shifts.\nWorks closely with support functions (HR, Finance, IT and Supply Chain) to build and secure support and resources for projects and initiatives. \nIdentify opportunities to reduce logistics cost and improve operations\nBudget and expense control\nAbility to build and maintain a strong team\nDemonstrate an ability to assess the impact of short-term decisions on the longer term business goals.\nSupervise and motivate a large staff of managers, employees and temporary workers.\nEnsure that customer's service expectations are met, including achieving all service levels metrics and quality performance goals\nGenerate, cultivate and communicate ideas for continual improvement of processes and activities across all areas of the DC operation.\nPrepare various reports and analyses as required.\nResearch and reconcile forecasted financial results with posted General Ledger results as part of the Month end reconciliation.\nFoster a strong culture of teamwork and high staff engagement\nbuilding a best-in-class safety operating environment and high quality.\n \nKey Performance Indicators & Conduct requirements:\nMeet budgeted commitments\nCustomer lates\nDepartmental SLA and TAT\nProductivity targets\nUnit economics\nZendesk tickets\n \nPersonal attributes:\nStrong operational person\nStrong systems affinity\nAbility to work on details / exception management\nTeam player\nAbility to engage with various levels in the company\nDriven on results, ambitious and go getter\nNumerate and financial mind\n \nCompetencies:\nVery strong operational mind set\nSelf-starter\nProblem solver, ability to think fast\nStrong negotiation skills\nTactical thinking and management skills\nDeep understanding of operations\nResponds quickly to changing situations and works well under pressure while maintaining individual team effectiveness.\nHigh degree of organizing and planning skills.\nLogical approach to analyzing problems and determining key issues.\nPersonal qualities that include being proactive and a strategic thinker.\nFocus on accuracy and attention to detail.\nAble to interact with people at all the highest level of the organization and from diverse backgrounds.\nGood interpersonal skills - works well with others, able to motivate a complex team with diverse skills\nMentoring and coaching skills\nFocused, self-motivated and target driven; determined to succeed.\nService oriented attitude and great customer facing skills.\nEntrepreneurial ability to identify and develop new opportunities\n \nQualifications:\nDegree or National Diploma in Supply chain; engineering; Logistics; management\nAt least 5-7 years senior managerial experience\nPrevious experience and exposure in a highly complexed and detailed environment\nExperience and exposure in warehousing environment\nStock management experience (inventory)\nProductivity improvement experience, reaching and exceeding targets\nBudget management experience (building; and managing)\n \nThe Environment:\ntakealot.com employees are entrepreneurial and dynamic, smart, customer-centric, fun and have the shared ambition of takealot.com being the leading e-commerce company in Africa.\nWe have fun, work hard, take ownership, work in teams to create solutions, and are always open to direct feedback/new ideas on where we can improve.\nWe are short on ego and high on output.\nWe are doers and not only thinkers, it\u2019s all in the execution after all.\nWe love what we do and what we are creating.\n \nWe seek to Employ an Extra Ordinary Mind who:\nis forthright but respectful\nis an expert at doing, who can not only design but also execute\nis analytical, able to use data to make decisions\nis competitive, self-directed and strive to be the BEST (GREAT requires a lot of work and does not only happen during business hours\nis passionate about the potential of e-commerce and delivering a world-class customer experience\nis entrepreneurial, thrives under change and accepts it is a constant and always looks for solutions to do something better and faster\nis business SMART. Able to think about problems from a business perspective using technical and product input\nis curious and challenge the status quo\nis innovative and enjoys iteration\nis collaborative\nwill be at the cutting edge of developing new concepts for takealot.com.\nthinks like an owner of the business.\nis SMART, has INTEGRITY and is HARDWORKING\n \nIf you meet the above you are an Extraordinary Mind so come and join us!\n \nTakealot is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We encourage applicants from the previously disadvantaged groups and people with disabilities, to apply.\n\nAPPLY NOW",
                "RISK AND SECURITY MANAGER\nat takealot.com\nDurban Kwa Zulu Natal\ntakealot.com, a leading South African online retailer, is looking for a highly talented Risk and Security Manager to join our Supply Chain Team in KZN DC.\nWe are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hard-working people with integrity to join us.  We offer a market related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won\u2019t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.\nThis position reports to the Head of Risk and Security Manager:\n \nYour responsibilities will include:\nManagement of Risk within Transport, Logistics and Fleet management\nManagement of Security and Service Providers\nPlan, design and implementing the risk management tactics\nRegularly audit all operational processes from a risk perspective\nDaily risk assessments and evaluations\nRisk auditing and reporting\nWeekly security audit and reporting\nBusiness continuity plan\nLoss control, exception management and investigations across all regional sites\nDevelop a network of intelligence sources to identify high loss areas and develop corrective actions\nOn-route risk management\nDashcam management and affiliated service providers\nManagement of the complete Health and Safety function for the site as required and stipulated by law and COVID protocol's\nInnovate and proactively anticipate Risk within Transport, Logistics and Fleet management\nRegularly engage with operational managers\n \nQualifications & Experience:\nRisk Management Qualification\nMinimum 5 -7 years in Middle Management Risk Management in a Logistics or Transport environment\nForensic qualification & experience preferable\nExposure of H&S management\n \nThe Environment:\ntakealot.com employees are entrepreneurial and dynamic, smart, customer-centric, fun and have the shared ambition of takealot.com being the leading e-commerce company in Africa.\nWe have fun, work hard, take ownership, work in teams to create solutions, and are always open to direct feedback/new ideas on where we can improve.\nWe are short on ego and high on output.\nWe are doers and not only thinkers, it\u2019s all in the execution after all.\nWe love what we do and what we are creating.\n \nWe seek to Employ an Extra Ordinary Mind who:\nis respectful but forthright\nis an expert at doing, who can not only design but also execute\nis analytical, able to use data to make decisions\nis competitive, self-directed and strive to be the BEST (GREAT requires a lot of work and does not only happen during business hours\nis passionate about the potential of e-commerce and delivering a world-class customer experience\nis entrepreneurial, thrives under change and accepts it is a constant and always looks for solutions to do something better and faster\nis business SMART. Able to think about problems from a business perspective using technical and product input;\nis curious and challenge the status quo\nis innovative and enjoys iteration\nis collaborative\nwill be at the cutting edge of developing new concepts for takealot.com\nthinks like an owner of the business\nis SMART, has INTEGRITY and is HARD WORKING\n \nIf you meet the above you are an Extraordinary Mind so come and join us!\n \nTakealot is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Applicants from the previously disadvantaged groups and people with disabilities will be given preference.\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "SITE AND SERVICES MANAGER\nat takealot.com \nDurban Kwa Zulu Natal\ntakealot.com, a leading South African online retailer, is looking for a highly talented Site and Services Manager to join our Supply Chain team in KZN DC.\nWe are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hardworking people with integrity to join us. We offer a market related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won\u2019t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.\nThe position reports to: General Manager: Operations\n \nYour responsibilities may include:\nMaking active decisions on fault legitimacy, including scrutiny of quotations and sign-off of services rendered\nWill be the line of contact for building infrastructure backup system such as generator, UPS, (24/7 availability)\nFirst line of contact with the land lord and/or any representative\nOversees maintenance, improvement and long-term planning development, including major building renovations and rehabilitation projects\nPrepares information for review and discussion with Management and other staff to select vendors\nLeads and manages facility projects to ensure best utilization of space, resources and safety for all employees\nCoordinates office improvements including day-to-day facility operations and critical systems such as, electrical, lighting, plumbing and conference room equipment\nPerforms routine maintenance and repair tasks such as painting walls, replacing light bulbs, installing A/V equipment, etc., as needed\nOversees the administration of contactor work (e.g. janitorial, building contractors, landscaping, gardening)\nTracks and executes facility and maintenance expense budgets\nAssures compliance with all applicable laws and codes related to facilities including OHSA, ISO and city ordinances\nReconciles and tracks third-party invoices and expenses\nMaintains records and vendor documents, such as contracts, service records and warranty information\nEnsures location and employees are in compliance & works with employees to identify issues and to resolve within the expected and agreed parameters\nMaintain a presentable facility and property at all times\nSupervising sub-contracted staff\nBuilding and grounds maintenance\nManage cleaning/hygiene suppliers and contracts\nCatering and vending management, including the management and upkeep of Canteen facility\nUtilities and communication infrastructure\n \nQualification and Attributes\nGrade 12\nDiploma or certificate in Facility Management\n8 or more years of related work and knowledge, required\nMust understand and be able to manage power systems, IT cabling, basic construction, alarm systems, Gardening Maintenance, etc.\nSolutions-oriented, can-do attitude; self-motivated\nStrong organizational & prioritization skills\nAttention to detail\nExcellent communication skills, both written and spoken\nAbility to interact with internal & external stakeholders at all levels\nComfortable with change and excellent team player\nComfortable with learning and adapting to new systems\nBe able to work in a pressured environment.\nBe able to complete tasks quickly & efficiently.\nBe willing to go the extra mile\n \nThe Environment:\ntakealot.com employees are entrepreneurial and dynamic, smart, customer-centric, fun and have the shared ambition of takealot.com being the leading e-commerce company in Africa.\nWe have fun, work hard, take ownership, work in teams to create solutions, and are always open to direct feedback/new ideas on where we can improve.\nWe are short on ego and high on output.\nWe are doers and not only thinkers, it\u2019s all in the execution after all.\nWe love what we do and what we are creating.\n \nWe seek to Employ an Extra Ordinary Mind who:\nis forthright but respectful\nis an expert at doing, who can not only design but also execute\nis analytical, able to use data to make decisions\nis competitive, self-directed and strive to be the BEST (GREAT requires a lot of work and does not only happen during business hours\nis passionate about the potential of e-commerce and delivering a world-class customer experience\nis entrepreneurial, thrives under change and accepts it is a constant and always looks for solutions to do something better and faster\nis business SMART. Able to think about problems from a business perspective using technical and product input\nis curious and challenge the status quo\nis innovative and enjoys iteration\nis collaborative\nwill be at the cutting edge of developing new concepts for takealot.com.\nthinks like an owner of the business.\nis SMART, has INTEGRITY and is HARDWORKING\n \nIf you meet the above you are an Extraordinary Mind so come and join us!\n \nTakealot is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Applicants from the previously disadvantaged groups and people with disabilities will be given preference.\n \nThank you for applying.\n \nYour application has been received and if there is a fit, someone will be getting back to you. Should you not hear from us within 2-4 weeks, please see your application as unsuccessful.\n \nPlease note that if you have a personal information access request or a deletion request in terms of the Protection of Information Act, that request can be sent to hr@takealot.com.\nTakealot Group Talent Team. \n\nAPPLY NOW",
                "BRANCH CONTROLLER\nat takealot.com\nSpringbok\n \ntakealot.com, a leading South African online retailer, is looking for a highly talented Branch Controller to join our team in Springbok. \nWe are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hardworking people with integrity to join us.  We offer a market related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won\u2019t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.\nThe Hub will be responsible for the dispatch, receipt and management of parcels within Takealot & Superblist. It\u2019s primary objective therefore centres around strict timelines, efficiency and cost effectiveness.\n \nThis position reports to the Hub Manager.\nYour responsibilities will include:\nBe responsible for the overall running of the facility and all other secondary roles which flow from this function\nEnsure operations costs are in line with budget\nEnsures the on-time delivery of product to/from the distribution centre\nResponsible for implementation and effective utilization of system(s) which will ensure that all product within the warehouse and/or entering or leaving the warehouse is accurately identified and distributed/delivered timeously\nEnsure efficient warehousing with timeous movement of product.\nExtracts data and generates reports which will assist in performance tracking and decision making.\nEnsure consistent application of Company policies and procedures.\nTrains and supervise employees to carry out the functions under their control.\nImplement and maintain health and safety standards\nMust continually work to promote the orderliness and cleanliness of the work area and other company standards\nIdentifies value-creation opportunities for the company in the movement and distribution of the product.\nWorks closely with senior management and Human Resources to resolve issues and ensure quality service to our customers.\nOversee maintenance, repairs, or replacements for machines.\nPerform all other duties as assigned.\n \nAttributes required:\nResults driven individual who has demonstrated ability working in a high performance environment.\nMust have good attention to details, and be able to manage the big picture and continuous changes in customer requests and deliveries of product.\nMust be able to manage multiple, complex tasks and deal easily with pressure on a day in and day out basis.\nGood written and oral communication skills.\nGood understanding of business principles and practices; can effectively manage the materials function with a bottom line result.\n \nQualifications:\nMatric qualification\nTertiary qualification advantageous\n3-5 years Logistics experience\n\n \nHow To Sell This Job\nThe Environment:\ncom employees are entrepreneurial and dynamic, smart, customer-centric, fun and have the shared ambition of takealot.com being the leading e-commerce company in Africa.\nWe have fun, work hard, take ownership, work in teams to create solutions, and are always open to direct feedback/new ideas on where we can improve.\nWe are short on ego and high on output.\nWe are doers and not only thinkers, it\u2019s all in the execution after all.\nWe love what we do and what we are creating.\n \nWe seek to Employ an Extra Ordinary Mind who:\nis forthright but respectful\nis an expert at doing, who can not only design but also execute\nis analytical, able to use data to make decisions\nis competitive, self-directed and strive to be the BEST (GREAT requires a lot of work and does not only happen during business hours\nis passionate about the potential of e-commerce and delivering a world-class customer experience\nis entrepreneurial, thrives under change and accepts it is a constant and always looks for solutions to do something better and faster\nis business SMART. Able to think about problems from a business perspective using technical and product input\nis curious and challenge the status quo\nis innovative and enjoys iteration\nis collaborative\nwill be at the cutting edge of developing new concepts for takealot.com.\nthinks like an owner of the business.\nis SMART, has INTEGRITY and is HARDWORKING\n \nIf you meet the above you are an Extraordinary Mind so come and join us!\n \nTakealot is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We encourage applicants from the previously disadvantaged groups and people with disabilities, to apply.\n\nAPPLY NOW"
