                " \n \n \n \nSEAMER MECHANIC\nSouth Africa\n \nBE THE FIRST TO APPLY\n \nJOB DESCRIPTION\nTHE JOB AT A GLANCE\nTo manage the maintenance of all production equipment to ensure production can run efficiently.\n \nRESPONSIBILITIES\nWHAT YOU WILL DO \nMaintenance of processing, packing and labelling Equipment in the plant.\nMake sure equipment is safe for production and the environment\nDaily routine checks, inspections, lubrication and minor adjustments.\nHourly Inspection of seaming quality and take necessary actions\nDaily condition monitoring of fillers, seamers and conveyors\nConduct equipment audit and plan task for maintenance\nConduct problem solving for all breakdowns\nUpdate operators workstation action log\nCondition of work bench, toolbox and cupboard \u2013 Apply 5S principle\nIdentify minor defects daily and problem solve sources of contamination\nEnsure all work orders are returned daily with correct feedback\nDo plant walkabouts every morning and generate action to improve equipment reliability\nImprove operator skill in your area of responsibility \n \nQUALIFICATIONS\nWHAT YOU\u2019LL BRING TO THE TABLE\n \nKey attributes and competencies\nCore knowledge \u2013 Experience in the operation and maintenance of seamers \u2013 Angelus seamers\nAcademic \u2013 Qualified and trade tested artisan (preferably a Fitter & Turner) with sound knowledge and experience on seamers.  Practical knowledge and experience of lathe work (turning) welding (arc, argon, gas, brazing & soldering) and cutting\nComputer literacy\nPractical knowledge and experience of a maintenance management system e.g. Pragma or DMS would be advantageous\nMust be prepared to work overtime and shifts\nAble to work in a team\nAbility to work under pressure\nProblem solving abilities and fault finding\nAttentive to detail, innovative and quality orientated\n \nEssential skills and qualification\nQualified Seamer Mechanic with trade test\nN3 qualification as a minimum requirement\n5 years as a seamer mechanic within the FMCG manufacturing\n \nABOUT US\nTiger Brands is proudly Africa\u2019s largest listed manufacturers of fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG). We impact lives every day with our iconic, award-winning brands. Our core business is the manufacture, market and distribute everyday branded food and beverages. Our products are relevant across every meal occasion and are well positioned to grow. \nBeing a food company means we\u2019re an intimate part of everybody's daily lives and that\u2019s why we get loud and proud about exploring further, roaring louder and growing together.\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \nJOB INFO\nJob Identification: 4541\nJob Category: Supply Chain\nApply Before: 02/26/2024, 09:07 AM\nDegree Level: Bachelor's Degree\nJob Schedule: Full time\nLocations: Johannesburg, 1459, ZA\n \n \n \n ",
