                " \n \nMILLWRIGHT\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 Harrismith\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: Certificate of Registration as an \u2018Installation Electrician\u2019.                                                                                            \n\nExperience: two years\u2019 experience in both electrical and mechanical disciplines.\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Millwright to be based in Harrimith Factory.\n\nIn this role you will be responsible to Install, maintain and improve both electrical and mechanical equipment. Ensure efficient, safe operation of machinery by setting and adjusting devices to within allowed tolerances.\n \nA day in the life of a Millwright:\nComplete the necessary administrative tasks for AMM, SHE, CDM and MDWT.\nInteract with production, Suppliers and contracting staff.\nCoaching and mentoring of technical operators and apprentices.\nCarry out the planned maintenance required on plant.\nIncumbent must be pro-active and prevent breakdowns on his/her patrols and shows initiative to continuously improve equipment performance \u2013 condition-based maintenance.\nEnsure that all work is performed in a Safe and Environmentally conscientious manner.\nIn both electrical and mechanical disciplines, install, service, repair and maintain existing and new equipment.\nAttend to electrical and mechanical faults/breakdowns within the factory.\nBasic troubleshooting on PLC\u2019s and SCADA systems.\nProgramming and faultfinding on VSD\u2019\u2019s and soft starters.\nProgramming and faultfinding on defined instrumentation and calibration.\nRoot cause analysis of repetitive faults; implement corrective measures.\nSteer \u2018Continuous Improvement\u2019 teams to improve equipment reliability and performance.\nMaintain high standard of work.\nEnsure machine availability for production targets to be met.\nUndertakes to work shift, standby and overtime as per company requirements.\nElectrical panels must be closed, always locked and kept in a neat and clean condition complete with a set of as built wiring diagrams.\nalways Adhering to Safe Working Permit procedures (e.g., confined space, working at height, hot work, LOTO etc.)\nEnsure any dangerous conditions to be made safe immediately.\nEnsure that during all work performed, food safety is never compromised.\nCorrect errors on electrical and mechanical drawings, update accordingly.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nBasic working knowledge of PLC\u2019s\nminimum of two years\u2019 experience in both electrical and mechanical disciplines. \nPreferably have a Certificate of Registration as an \u2018Installation Electrician\u2019.  Served Apprenticeship and qualified with a Millwright Trade Test Certificate (Electromechanician.) \n \nHarrismith, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \nOFFICE SALES REPRESENTATIVE GAUTENG\nWe are the Nestl\u00e9 Nespresso SA Company and are proud to be one of the fastest growing operating unit of Nestl\u00e9. Our passionate, entrepreneurial-minded team has transformed Nespresso into the reference in portioned coffee and one of the world\u2019s most trusted brands. Our growth comes from our commitment to research and development in order to pioneer and be the reference in the portioned coffee sector to provide the very highest quality coffees that could be enjoyed in the comfort of consumers' own homes and also savored at out-of-home locations, such as restaurants, hotels, offices and luxury retail businesses. We guarantee quality by taking a careful, thoughtful approach in how we source our ingredients, produce and market our premium coffee products. With corporate headquarters in Lausanne, Switzerland, Nespresso is present in over 60 countries and counts over 12,000 employees worldwide. To learn more visit www.nespresso.com.\n \nJob Title: Nespresso Office Sales Representative\nLocation: Bryanston\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9 Nespresso\nQualifications: Completed Matric\nExperience: 3 years\u2019 experience in sales and new business development with a proven track record\nClosing date: 19 February 2024\n \nPosition Summary\nAcquire new customers in the strategic segment and/or evolve the business with existing customers in the assigned geographical territory to deliver agreed objectives/targets.\n \nA day in the life of an Office Sales Representative\n \nAligned with the sales field plan, identify sales opportunities within designated territory\nIdentify and contact prospects using diverse methods and tools (cold calling/visit, social media, events.\nAcquire new customers by following the Nespresso B2B Office guidelines\nUse of CRM system to manage leads, grow / maintain existing customers\nLiaise with B2B Sales Support and Customer Care teams to ensure flawless execution of lead management activities.\nIncrease business with existing customers / maximize penetration rate in a customer (share of throat)\nProvide market intelligence to the sales team\nLiaise with B2B Sales Support and Customer Care teams to ensure flawless execution of customer lifecycle management.\nCollect accurate inputs to ensure compliance of the sales process.\nCompliance with Nestl\u00e9 and Nespresso business principles and policies including Nestl\u00e9 Nespresso trade policy, local Sales policy, local Trade Terms, Safety, and legal regulations.\n \nWhat will make you successful\nCompleted Matric\nGood command in English communication with computer skills (MS-Office applications)\nResult-oriented with strong selling, presentation, and negotiation skills\nPassionate, persevere and self-motivated to achieve the challenging sales target\nEnergized by tough challenges and is a team player\n \nPeople are at the heart of our success \u2013 all 14,000 of them. We actively cultivate diversity, inclusion and belonging in the workplace. We celebrate individuality, believing that your authenticity and uniqueness can help us to grow and thrive together.\n \nBryanston, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \nCOFFEE AND ENGINEERING SPECIALIST\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 Estcourt\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: BSc in Chemical/Mechanical/Food Science\nExperience: Experience in coffee or beverage manufacturing processes\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Coffee Specialist to be based in Estcourt Factory. \n\nIn this role you will be responsible to develop and implementing process strategies, managing process resources, optimizing current processes, maintaining process documents. Design and testing of new processes, systems, and standards to maintain the efficiency of production.\nA day in the life of a Coffee Specialist:\nThroughout the process and with the checks carried out, the specialist will observe whether the parameters are adjusted to the dictated running conditions or must make variations for the proper functioning of the installation.\nKnow the different technologies of extraction, evaporation and spray drying process with strong governance of Best Manufacturing Practices per section.\nLead, coordinate and implement continuous improvement initiatives in manufacturing activities in the factory.\nProvide technical support to the factory to optimize process performance and implement new technologies.\nSupport and identify requirements for development and industrialization of new products.\nManufacturing Excellence:\nIdentify opportunities and lead process improvement initiatives to reduce manufacturing costs and optimize process efficiency.\nLead or support initiatives to implement and sustain best manufacturing practices.\nProvide technical support to factory on identifying root causes of problems on manufacturing and product quality issues and give recommendations.\nIncrease knowledge within factory staff through training and development of Subject Matter Experts on key technologies.\nLead and deliver key Idea to Launch projects. \nLead initiatives on harmonization of recipes and materials for cost optimization.\nLead material flow mass balance across processes to identify and optimize on manufacturing losses.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nBSc in Chemical/Mechanical/Food Science\nExperience in coffee or beverage manufacturing processes\nExperience in people management\nExpertise in product development or R&D with strong knowledge of the product category and its technologies\n \nEstcourt, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nCOFFEE AND ENGINEERING SPECIALIST\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 Estcourt\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: BSc in Chemical/Mechanical/Food Science\nExperience: Experience in coffee or beverage manufacturing processes\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Coffee Specialist to be based in Estcourt Factory. \n\nIn this role you will be responsible to develop and implementing process strategies, managing process resources, optimizing current processes, maintaining process documents. Design and testing of new processes, systems, and standards to maintain the efficiency of production.\n \nA day in the life of a Coffee Specialist:\nThroughout the process and with the checks carried out, the specialist will observe whether the parameters are adjusted to the dictated running conditions or must make variations for the proper functioning of the installation.\nKnow the different technologies of extraction, evaporation and spray drying process with strong governance of Best Manufacturing Practices per section.\nLead, coordinate and implement continuous improvement initiatives in manufacturing activities in the factory.\nProvide technical support to the factory to optimize process performance and implement new technologies.\nSupport and identify requirements for development and industrialization of new products.\nManufacturing Excellence:\nIdentify opportunities and lead process improvement initiatives to reduce manufacturing costs and optimize process efficiency.\nLead or support initiatives to implement and sustain best manufacturing practices.\nProvide technical support to factory on identifying root causes of problems on manufacturing and product quality issues and give recommendations.\nIncrease knowledge within factory staff through training and development of Subject Matter Experts on key technologies.\nLead and deliver key Idea to Launch projects. \nLead initiatives on harmonization of recipes and materials for cost optimization.\nLead material flow mass balance across processes to identify and optimize on manufacturing losses.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nBSc in Chemical/Mechanical/Food Science\nExperience in coffee or beverage manufacturing processes\nExperience in people management\nExpertise in product development or R&D with strong knowledge of the product category and its technologies\n \nEstcourt, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nMICROBIOLOGIST\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nLocation: Clayville\nQualification: bachelor\u2019s Degree/Diploma in Microbiology, Food technology, and related field\nExperience: 3 years\u2019 experience in Microbiological laboratory\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Microbiologist to be based in Clayville. \nIn this role you will be responsible to carry out testing of samples according to procedure in excellent quality and timely manner. Ensures that all equipment is properly maintained, methods are verified for the scope of usage, executed, and documented as per quality system and accreditation requirements. Extends skills and competencies according to sections needs and development plan contributing to continuous improvement in the laboratory.\n \nA day in the life of a Microbiologist\nSafety:\nResponsible for own safety and safety of others as per NQAC SHE rules.\nQuality:\nExecutes analytical testing and validates results according to competency matrix.\nTakes part in method implementation (validation, verification, matrix extension), method and GLP audits.\nMonitors analytical methods and environment as per internal procedures.\nActively supports operations meeting customer expectations regarding timely results delivery. \nExecute and maintain ICP\u2019s for method and equipment as per procedures including calibration schedule and assists in continuously improving equipment ICPs. \nMonitors and maintains necessary inventory for chemicals and materials.\nQuality System:\nDefine and update the specific quality procedures, instructions and tools which are directly related to their analyses and tests.\nExecute and maintain change management as per procedure.\nActively involved in problem solving       \nNCE:\nActively involved in relevant NCE activities including continuous improvement.\n                                                                \nWhat will make you successful?\nbachelor\u2019s Degree/Diploma in Microbiology, Food technology, and related field\n3 years\u2019 experience in Microbiological laboratory\nGood knowledge in quality management system ISO/IEC 17025\nIntermediate in spoken and written English and computer skill\nPrevious experience on ELISA or PCR platform.\nHigh level of attention to detail.\nKey Experiences:\n \nNA, ZA, 1665\n \nAPPLY NOW\n \n \n \n ",
                "TEMP PROJECT ENGINEER\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 East London\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: Degree or Diploma in Mechanical Engineering/BSc\nExperience: 3 years\u2019 experience in Capital Investment and Project development and implementation in food industry.\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Project Engineer to be based in East London Factory.\nIn this role you will be responsible to Manage and / or perform the design, implementation and start-up phases of capital investment projects on the manufacturing site, within the defined scope of responsibility or specialization. Ensure that the objectives of the investment project charter, design specifications and Nestl\u00e9 standards are implemented and adhered to.\n \nA day in the life of a Project Engineer:\n\nBefore starting the project design phase:\nSupport the End-to-End Project Manager and Project Engineering Manager in developing the investment project charter and ensure that it is strictly followed throughout the project.\nDuring project design phase:\nExecute the basic and detailed design of the project based on Nestl\u00e9 Corporate Business Principles, Nestl\u00e9 standards, local regulations, the defined User Requirements Specifications and the TPM characteristics of a unit operation (safety, quality, affordability, maintainability, operability, and reliability). Ensure by design the workers, and operators, safety during both the construction and the ongoing operation of the plant.\nDuring the project implementation phase:\nEnsure that the engineering side of the project is implemented (e.g., buildings, equipment erections, piping, utilities, etc.) in accordance with the defined timing, cost and quality, the URS and the characteristics of a unit operation. And that all the elements of the project (including technical people training, as needed) in performed in such a way that safety is always guaranteed on the whole project site and that a vertical start-up is assured. Select and qualify contractors and coordinate their activities. Ensure that Nestl\u00e9 standards are applied.\nDuring the start-up phase of the project:\n Support the start-up manager and their team to ensure a smooth transition to operations after the qualification and verification of the installation.\nContribute to and support the preparation and distributing the engineering project documentation, including the engineering part of the project final report and provide feedback to the Maintenance Prevention System.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nManufacturing projects management experience \n3 years\u2019 experience in capital investment projects development and implementation in food industry.\nDetermination of methods to minimize the likelihood of injuries or damages to people and/or equipment (SH&E)\n Factory operations (as required)\n \nEast London, ZA\nAPPLY NOW",
                "TEAM LEADER NUTRITION\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 Harrismith\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: Degree/Diploma in Food sciences, Chemistry or Chemical/Mechanical engineering.\nExperience: 3 years or more experience in similar role\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Team Leader to be based in Harrismith Factory. \n\nIn this role you will be responsible to manage of designated team, plant, and materials in a culture of performance monitoring, review and action, open communication, employee involvement, employee relations, continuous improvement in support of achieving organization mission and objectives. To ensure employee safety, product quality and performance while delivering on time the shift production plan.\nA day in the life of a Team Leader:\nEnsure the timely deployment of People development plan and assure the competencies of his/her team as per the agreed plan with PM (proper training inc. equipment, safety procedures, hygiene) Enforce strict compliance to standard operating procedures (SOPs) by all personnel within the shift. \nCoach employees to fulfil and exceed the requirements of the job through NCE approach.\nEnsure that the working areas are kept clean and are maintained in working order including all installations in accordance with Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP).\nCheck and enforce personnel hygiene & safety e.g., protective clothing (uniform), shoe change & hand wash.\nEnsure continuous line Controls and immediate corrective action to assure prescribed quality and to ensure compliance with manufacturing instructions.\nEnsure ongoing smooth operations of factory through effective employee and industrial relations management.\nEnsure that there is an adequate distribution of skills to enable production plan to be achieved effectively.\nEnsure timely launch of new products to the Market as per agreed with the business unit.\nEnsure adequate maintenance of the installations in coordination with quality, engineering & administration.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nDegree/Diploma in Food sciences, Chemistry or Chemical/Mechanical engineering.\n3 years or more experience in similar role.\nExperience in FMCG will add as an advantage.\nDemonstration of leadership ability by leading a project within a factory environment.\nDemonstration of Leadership skills in positively confronting inappropriate behavior and using everyday coaching to ensure involvement of the workforce.\n \nHarrismith, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW",
                "BUSINESS PROCESS CONTROL SPECIALIST\nLocation: Nestl\u00e9 Harrismith\nCompany: Nestl\u00e9\nQualification: Diploma/Degree in Production Management/ Chemical Engineering\nExperience: 3-5 years\u2019 experience.\n \nPosition Summary\nWith a history spanning over 150 years, Nestl\u00e9 didn\u2019t become the world\u2019s leading food and beverages brand by chance. Perfection is at the heart of what we do, and our people are always looking for the next big idea to cement our status. We are now looking for a Business Process Control Specialist to be based in Harrismith Factory. \n\nIn this role you will be responsible to ensure efficient of the production section in terms of administration, planning control, best practice application, PSA stock management & SAP data accuracies. Ensure that the Globe template and T&P processes are fit in order to meet business requirements. Advise, train & support team leaders and establish formal communication channel with FICO & QA.\nA day in the life of a Business Process Control Specialist:\nRelease process orders daily and instruct factory planner with alternatives.\nSupervise all capturing of SAM/ downtime, run time and all stoppages.  \nControl variances (labour and material) and implementation of appropriate action.\nChair and mange weekly variance meetings with costing (ADMIN) department.\nWeekly and monthly stock counting of PSA(141,145,172).\nSupervise the use of rework into the product (ensure FEFO) applies.\nEnsure correct recording consumption of rework per process order.\nClose off PI sheet daily with 100% accuracy.\nSupervise the rework champions operations.\nTrain end-users in rework management according to T&P, MH BP.\n \nWhat will make you successful?\nDiploma/Degree in Production Management/ Chemical Engineering.\n3-5 years\u2019 experience.\nknowledge of factory end-to-end processes.\nExperience with process definition within the T&P application environment (SAP).\n \nHarrismith, ZA\n \nAPPLY NOW"
